  "texts": [
    "Specifically, several works consider blocking communication through predefined or learnable decisions of whether to communicate or not, while aiming to differentiate useful communicated information [38, 40, 48, 73, 76, 78, 81-84, 91, 92].",
    "We also put those works under this category as they do not explicitly assume that communication is limited by cost.",
    "Constrained communicationIn this category, communication processes are explicitly constrained by cost or noise.",
    "Thus, agents need to utilize communication resources efficiently to promote learning.",
    "We further identify two practical concerns that have been considered in the literature.• Limited Bandwidth."
  ]
}